  Abstraction  
    Abstraction 

    Identifying important aspects while ignoring details (separating important concerns)  Abstraction permeates software development  From natural language descriptions to mathematical models  From requirements to code  one specification but many realizations    From products to process    Models are abstractions of reality  Abstraction depends on purpose or point of view       
 
   

